  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 200 °C (400 °F).",
    "Brush both sides of each bread slice with olive oil and place on a baking sheet.",
    "Bake for 5 minutes, until the bread is lightly toasted.",
    "In a small bowl, combine crumbled feta, smoked paprika, oregano, minced garlic, cayenne pepper, grated Parmesan, lemon zest, and a squeeze of lemon juice. Season with salt and pepper.",
    "Remove the toast from the oven and spoon the feta mixture over each slice, spreading evenly.",
    "Return to the oven and bake for an additional 5–7 minutes, until the feta is golden and crispy.",
    "Remove from oven, sprinkle chopped parsley on top, and let cool for a minute.",
    "Serve immediately as a warm, savory snack."
  ],
